s\n|-\n|1878\n|[[Duke of Magenta (horse)|Duke of Magenta]]\n|[[R. Wyndham Walden]]\n|[[George L. Lorillard]]\n|-\n|1877\n|[[Baden-Baden (horse)|Baden-Baden]]\n|[[James Williams (horseman)|James Williams]]\n|[[William Backhouse Astor Jr.|William B. Astor Jr.]]\n|-\n|1876\n|[[Vigil (horse)|Vigil]] \u2021\n|[[Evert V. Snedecker]]\n|[[Dwyer Brothers Stable]]\n|-\n|1876\n|[[Vagrant (horse)|Vagrant]] \u2021\n|[[A. Davis Pryor]]\n|[[William Backhouse Astor Jr.|William B. Astor Jr.]]\n|-\n|1875\n|[[Tom Ochiltree]]\n|[[R. Wyndham Walden]]\n|[[John F. Chamberlain]]\n|-\n|1874\n|[[Acrobat (horse)|Acrobat]]\n|[[Charles S. Lloyd]]\n|K. W. Sears\n|-\n|1872\n|[[Joe Daniels (horse)|Joe Daniels]]\n|[[David McDaniel (horseman)|David McDaniel]]\n|[[David McDaniel (horseman)|David McDaniel]]\n|-\n|1871\n|[[Harry Bassett (horse)|Harry Bassett]]\n|[[David McDaniel (horseman)|David McDaniel]]\n|[[David McDaniel (horseman)|David McDaniel]]\n|}\n\n<small>A \u2021 designates co champion three-year-olds.</small>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n* [https://archive.is/20120525105712/http://www.tra-online.com/eclipse.html The Eclipse Awards at the Thoroughbred Racing Associations of America, Inc.]\n* [http://www.bloodhorse.com/eclipsewinners/pdf/History_Charts.pdf ''The Bloodhorse.com'' Champion's history charts]\n* [http://www.tbheritage.com/TurfHallmarks/Champs/AmChamp3yoMale.html American Champion Three-Year-Old Male]\n\n{{Eclipse Awards}}\n\n{{short description|Award for American racehorses}}\n\n[[Category:Horse racing awards]]\n[[Category:Horse racing in the United States]]\n", "text_old": "The '''American Champion Three-Year-Old Male Horse''' is an [[United States|American]] [[Thoroughbred]] [[horse racing]] honor awarded annually in Thoroughbred [[flat racing]]. It became part of the [[Eclipse Award]]s program in 1971.\n\nThe award originated in 1936 when both ''Turf & Sports Digest'' (TSD) the ''[[Daily Racing Form]]'' (DRF) began naming an annual champion. Starting in 1950, the Thoroughbred Racing Associations (TRA) began naming its own champion. The following list provides the name of the horses chosen by these organizations. The only disagreement came in 1968, when Turf & Sports Digest named [[Forward Pass (horse)|Forward Pass]] as champion whereas the other two organizations voted for [[Stage Door Johnny]].\n\nChampions from 1887 through 1935 were selected retrospectively by a panel of experts as published by ''[[The Blood-Horse magazine]]''.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.bloodhorse.com/eclipsewinners/pdf/History_Charts.pdf |title=Archived copy |access-date=August 27, 2008 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120904120526/http://www.bloodhorse.com/eclipsewinners/pdf/History_Charts.pdf |archive-date=September 4, 2012 |url-status=bot: unknown |df=mdy-all }}</ref>\n\nThere were Co-Champions chosen retrospectively for 1876, 1882, 1885, 1886, 1888, 1893, 1894, 1904, 1906, 1917, 1923, and 1932.\n\nThe ''Daily Racing Form'', the Thoroughbred Racing Associations, and the National Turf Writers Association all joined forces in 1971 to create the Eclipse Award.\n\nAs of 2018, Bob Baffert won the award 9 times as a trainer. No other train won the award more than twice.<ref>{{cite news|first=Jon|last=White|url=https://www.xpressbet.com/component/content/article/11-xb360/xb-blog/4021-an-extraordinary-feat-largely-unnoticed |title=An Extraordinary Feat Largely Unnoticed |publisher=Xpressbet |date=January 30, 2019 |accessdate=2019-01-30}}</ref>\n\n==Honorees==\n\n===Eclipse Awards===\n{| class = \"wikitable sortable\" | border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse: collapse; font-size:90%\"\n|-  style=\"background:#987654; text-align:center;\"\n! style=\"width:42px;\"| '''Year'''<br>\n! style=\"width:175px;\"| '''Horse'''<br>\n! style=\"width:165px;\"| '''Trainer'''<br>\n! style=\"width:250px;\"| '''Owner'''<br>\n|-\n|2019\n| [[Maximum Security (horse)|Maximum Security]]\n| [[Jason Servis]]\n| Gary and Mary West\n|-\n|2018\n| [[Justify (horse)|Justify]]\n| [[Bob Baffert]]\n| China Horse Club, Head of Plains Partners, Starlight Racing 7 [[WinStar Farm]]\n|-\n|2017\n|[[West Coast (horse)|West Coast]]\n|[[Bob Baffert]]\n|Gary and Mary West\n|-\n|2016\n|[[Arrogate]]\n|[[Bob Baffert]]\n|[[Juddmonte Farms]]\n|-\n|2015\n|[[American Pharoah]]\n|[[Bob Baffert]]\n|[[Zayat Stables]]\n|-\n|2014\n|[[California Chrome]]\n|[[Art Sherman]]\n|[[Ownership of California Chrome|Steven Coburn, Perry Martin]]\n|-\n|2013\n|[[Will Take Charge]]\n|[[D. Wayne Lukas]]\n|Willis D. Horton\n|-\n|2012\n|[[I'll Have Another]]\n|[[Doug F. O'Neill]]\n|[[J. Paul Reddam]]\n|-\n|2011\n|[[Animal Kingdom (horse)|Animal Kingdom]]\n|[[H. Graham Motion]]\n|[[Team Valor]]\n|-\n|2010\n|[[Lookin At Lucky]]\n|[[Bob Baffert]]\n|[[Mike Pegram]], Karl Watson & Paul Weitman\n|-\n|2009\n|[[Summer Bird]]\n|[[Tim Ice]]\n|Dr. K. K. & Dr. V. Devi Jayaraman\n|-\n|2008\n|[[Big Brown]]\n|[[Richard E. Dutrow Jr.]]\n|[[IEAH Stables]] & Paul Pompa Jr.\n|-\n|2007\n|[[Curlin]]\n|[[Steve Asmussen]]\n|[[Jess Stonestreet Jackson Jr.|Stonestreet Stables]] ''et al.''\n|-\n|2006\n|[[Bernardini (horse)|Bernardini]]\n|[[Thomas Albertrani]]\n|[[Darley Stable]]\n|-\n|2005\n|[[Afleet Alex]]\n|[[Timothy F. Ritchey]]\n|Cash Is King Stable\n|-\n|2004\n|[[Smarty Jones]]\n|[[John Servis]]\n|Roy & Patricia Chapman\n|-\n|2003\n|[[Funny Cide]]\n|[[Barclay Tagg]]\n|[[Sackatoga Stable]]\n|-\n|2002\n|[[War Emblem]]\n|[[Bob Baffert]]\n|[[Russell L. Reineman|R. L. Reineman]]/[[The Thoroughbred Corp.]]\n|-\n|2001\n|[[Point Given]]\n|[[Bob Baffert]]\n|[[The Thoroughbred Corp.]]\n|-\n|2000\n|[[Tiznow]]\n|[[Jay M. Robbins]]\n|Michael Cooper & Cecilia Straub-Rubens\n|-\n|1999\n|[[Charismatic (horse)|Charismatic]]\n|[[D. Wayne Lukas]]\n|[[Robert B. Lewis|Bob & Beverly Lewis]]\n|-\n|1998\n|[[Real Quiet]]\n|[[Bob Baffert]]\n|[[Michael E. Pegram]]\n|-\n|1997\n|[[Silver Charm]]\n|[[Bob Baffert]]\n|[[Robert B. Lewis|Bob & Beverly Lewis]]\n|-\n|1996\n|[[Skip Away]]\n|[[Sonny Hine]]\n|[[Sonny Hine|Carolyn Hine]]\n|-\n|1995\n|[[Thunder Gulch]]\n|[[D. Wayne Lukas]]\n|[[Michael Tabor]]\n|-\n|1994\n|[[Holy Bull]]\n|[[Warren A. Croll Jr.]]\n|[[Warren A. Croll Jr.]]\n|-\n|1993\n|[[Prairie Bayou]]\n|[[Thomas Bohannan]]\n|[[Loblolly Stable]]\n|-\n|1992\n|[[A.P. Indy]]\n|[[Neil D. Drysdale]]\n|[[Tomonori Tsurumaki]]\n|-\n|1991\n|[[Hansel (horse)|Hansel]]\n|[[Frank L. Brothers]]\n|[[Joe Allbritton|Lazy Lane Farm]]\n|-\n|1990\n|[[Unbridled]]\n|[[Carl Nafzger]]\n|[[Frances A. Genter]]\n|-\n|1989\n|[[Sunday Silence]]\n|[[Charles E. Whittingham]]\n|[[H-G-W Partners]]\n|-\n|1988\n|[[Risen Star]]\n|[[Louie Roussel III]]\n|Ronnie Lamarque & Louie Roussel III\n|-\n|1987\n|[[Alysheba]]\n|[[Jack Van Berg]]\n|Dorothy & Pamela Scharbauer\n|-\n|1986\n|[[Snow Chief]]\n|[[Melvin F. Stute]]\n|Carl Grinstead & Ben Rochelle\n|-\n|1985\n|[[Spend A Buck]]\n|[[Cam Gambolati]]\n|Hunter Farm\n|-\n|1984\n|[[Swale (horse)|Swale]]\n|[[Woody Stephens]]\n|[[Claiborne Farm]]\n|-\n|1983\n|[[Slew o' Gold]]\n|[[Sidney Watters Jr.]]\n|[[Equusequity Stable]]\n|-\n|1982\n|[[Conquistador Cielo]]\n|[[Woody Stephens]]\n|[[Henryk de Kwiatkowski]]\n|-\n|1981\n|[[Pleasant Colony]]\n|[[John P. Campo]]\n|[[Buckland Farm]]\n|-\n|1980\n|[[Temperence Hill]]\n|[[Joseph B. Cantey]]\n|[[Loblolly Stable]]\n|-\n|1979\n|[[Spectacular Bid]]\n|[[Bud Delp]]\n|Hawksworth Farm\n|-\n|1978\n|[[Affirmed]]\n|[[Laz Barrera]]\n|[[Louis Wolfson|Harbor View Farm]]\n|-\n|1977\n|[[Seattle Slew]]\n|[[William H. Turner Jr.]]\n|Karen & Mickey Taylor\n|-\n|1976\n|[[Bold Forbes]]\n|[[Laz Barrera]]\n|[[Est\u00e9ban Rodriguez Tizol]]\n|-\n|1975\n|[[Wajima (horse)|Wajima]]\n|[[Stephen A. DiMauro]]\n|East-West Stable\n|-\n|1974\n|[[Little Current (horse)|Little Current]]\n|[[Lou Rondinello]]\n|[[Darby Dan Farm]]\n|-\n|1973\n|[[Secretariat (horse)|Secretariat]]\n|[[Lucien Laurin]]\n|[[Penny Chenery|Meadow Stable]]\n|-\n|1972\n|[[Key to the Mint]]\n|[[J. Elliott Burch]]\n|[[Rokeby Stables]]\n|-\n|1971\n|[[Canonero II]]\n|[[Juan Arias (horse trainer