{"title_page": "Charli D'Amelio", "text_new": "{{Use mdy dates|date=February 2020}}\n{{pp-blp|small=yes}}\n{{Short description|American social media personality}}\n\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Charli D'Amelio\n| image              = \n| caption            = \n| birth_name         = \n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age|2004|5|1}}\n| birth_place        = [[Norwalk, Connecticut]], U.S.<ref name=\"norwalk\">{{Cite web|url=https://dailyvoice.com/connecticut/norwalk/lifestyle/norwalk-15-year-old-dancer-surges-to-stardom-on-social-media-with-five-million-followers/779708/|title=Norwalk 15-Year-Old Dancer Surges To Stardom On Social Media With Five Million Followers|date=November 25, 2019|website=Norwalk Daily Voice|language=en|access-date=February 16, 2020}}</ref>\n| occupation         = {{hlist|[[Social media personality]]|Dancer}}\n| years_active       = 2019\u2013present\n| known_for          = [[TikTok]]\n| relatives          = Dixie D'Amelio (sister)<ref name=\"nbcnews\">{{cite web |url=https://www.nbcnews.com/pop-culture/viral/meet-charli-d-amelio-tiktok-s-newest-viral-teen-celebrity-n1092626 |title=Meet Charli D'Amelio, TikTok's newest viral teen celebrity |last=Rosenblatt |first=Kalhan |publisher=[[NBC News]] |date=November 28, 2019 |access-date=January 25, 2020}}</ref>\nHeidi D'Amelio (mother)<br>Marc D'Amelio (father)<ref name=\"nbcnews\" />\n}}\n\n'''Charli D'Amelio''' (born May 1, 2004)<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cosmopolitan.com/entertainment/celebs/amp31019692/who-is-charli-damelio-tiktok/|title=TikTok Star Charli D\u2019Amelio Has No Idea How She Got So Famous|work=[[Cosmopolitan (magazine)|Cosmopolitan]]|access-date=March 21, 2020}}</ref> is an American [[social media personality]] and dancer, who creates videos on [[TikTok]]. As of April 2020, she has accumulated over 47.2 million followers on the social platform, and has been called the \"reigning queen of TikTok\" by the ''[[New York Times]]''.<ref name=\"nyt\">{{cite web |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/01/03/style/hype-house-los-angeles-tik-tok.html |title=Hype House and the Los Angeles TikTok Mansion Gold Rush |last=Lorenz |first=Taylor |date=January 3, 2020 |website=[[The New York Times]] |access-date=January 25, 2020}} </ref> She is the [[List of most-followed TikTok accounts|most-followed]] individual on the platform.\n\n==Career==\nD'Amelio's career began on [[TikTok]] in the summer of 2019 with uploaded dance videos. She has since acquired over 43.6 million [[TikTok]] followers,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.tiktok.com/@charlidamelio?isUniqueId=true&sec_uid=|title=charli d\u2019amelio on TikTok|website=TikTok|language=en|access-date=2020-03-28}}</ref> 11.9 million [[Instagram]] followers,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/charlidamelio/|title=charli d\u2019amelio (@charlidamelio) \u2022 Instagram photos and videos|website=www.instagram.com|language=en|access-date=2020-03-28}}</ref> 2.58 million [[YouTube]] subscribers,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCi3OE-aN09WOcN9d2stCvPg|title=charli d'amelio|website=YouTube|language=en|access-date=2020-03-28}}</ref> and over 846 thousand [[Twitter]] followers.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/charlidamelio|title=charli d\u2019amelio (@charlidamelio) {{!}} Twitter|website=twitter.com|language=en|access-date=2020-03-28}}</ref> In just 10 months, she became the [[List of most-followed TikTok accounts|most-followed account]] on the social media platform [[TikTok]]. She surpassed the previous most-followed individual, [[Loren Gray]], on March 25, 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://en.m.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_most-followed_TikTok_accounts|title=List of most-followed TikTok accounts - Wikipedia|website=en.m.wikipedia.org|language=en|access-date=2020-03-27}}</ref>\n\nIn January 2020, D'Amelio signed with talent agency [[United Talent Agency|UTA]].<ref name=\"times\">{{cite web |url=https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/hollywood-agency-uta-signs-tiktoks-teen-star-charli-damelio-qchbk3v6c |title=Hollywood agency UTA signs TikTok\u2019s teen star Charli D\u2019Amelio |last=Fortson |first=Danny |date=January 19, 2020 |website=[[The Sunday Times]] |access-date=January 25, 2020}}</ref> She then landed a spot in a Super Bowl commercial for Sabra Hummus along with other celebrities.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.theverge.com/2020/2/2/21119668/tiktok-super-bowl-ad-charli-damelio-hyundai-mountain-dew-justin-bieber|title=TikTok has its Super Bowl moment in more ways than one|last=Alexander|first=Julia|date=2020-02-02|website=The Verge|language=en|access-date=2020-02-18}}</ref> She was invited to attend Super Bowl LIV and meet [[Jennifer Lopez]] to create the viral [[TikTok]] challenge \"J Lo Super Bowl Challenge.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.etonline.com/tiktok-star-charli-damelio-on-her-dream-come-true-dance-with-jennifer-lopez-exclusive-140744|title=TikTok Star Charli D'Amelio on Her Dance With Jennifer Lopez|website=Entertainment Tonight|language=en-US|access-date=2020-02-18}}</ref>\n\nShe is a part of the collaborative [[TikTok]] web group \"[[The Hype House|Hype House]]\" along with 18 others, including Chase Hudson, Avani Gregg, [[Addison Rae Easterling]], and sister Dixie D'Amelio.<ref name=\"nyt\" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.insider.com/hype-house-members-charli-d-amelio-lilhuddy-tiktok-los-angeles-2020-1|title=TikTok's Hype House is home to some of the app's biggest stars, including Charli D'Amelio. Who are the other 20 members?|last=Perrett|first=Connor|website=Insider|access-date=2020-02-18}}</ref>\n\nShe has been invited to perform at the NBA All-Star game, performing with fellow [[The Hype House|Hype House]] members [[Addison Rae]], her sister Dixie, and creator of the \"renegade\" dance, Jalaiah Harmon.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.insider.com/renegade-creator-danced-charli-damelio-nba-all-star-game-2020-2|title=The original 'Renegade' dance creator Jalaiah Harmon collaborated with Charli D'Amelio and performed at the NBA All-Star Game|last=Harris|first=Margot|website=Insider|access-date=2020-02-18}}</ref> On March 27, 2020, D'Amelio collaborated on [[YouTube]] with actor [[Noah Schnapp]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://m.youtube.com/watch?v=NL9Oub28wUU&feature=youtu.be|title=Noah Schnapp Teaches Me How To Act! {{!}} Charli D\u2019Amelio|last=D\u2019Amelio|first=Charli|date=March 27, 2020|website=YouTube|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=March 28, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nHer immediate family includes politician and father, Marc D'Amelio, her mother, Heidi D'Amelio, and her sister, Dixie D'Amelio.<ref name=\"nbcnews\">{{cite web |url=https://www.nbcnews.com/pop-culture/viral/meet-charli-d-amelio-tiktok-s-newest-viral-teen-celebrity-n1092626 |title=Meet Charli D'Amelio, TikTok's newest viral teen celebrity |last=Rosenblatt |first=Kalhan |publisher=[[NBC News]] |date=November 28, 2019 |access-date=January 25, 2020}}</ref>\n\nD'Amelio has been subject to bullying and body shaming.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.insider.com/charli-dixie-damelio-tik-tok-biggest-stars-cyberbullying-video-2020-2|title=One of TikTok's biggest stars say she gets hundreds of thousands of hate comments every week, often focusing on her body and weight|last=|first=|date=|website=dx.doi.org|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-02-18}}</ref> She and her sister have partnered with [[UNICEF]], speaking out against online bullying and the perils of finding fame on the platform.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.insider.com/charli-dixie-damelio-tik-tok-biggest-stars-cyberbullying-video-2020-2|title=One of TikTok's biggest stars say she gets hundreds of thousands of hate comments every week, often focusing on her body and weight|last=Lustig|first=Hanna|website=Insider|access-date=2020-02-18}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{TikTok}}\n* {{Instagram}}\n* {{IMDb name}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Damelio, Charli}}\n[[Category:2004 births]]\